    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94115 Exchange/5–945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-09">May 9,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received May 9—8:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2671. American Interests, Japan. Legation’s 1795, March 26. Swiss note May 5
                    states that Gorgé during conversation with Minister Suzuki, Chief of Foreign
                    Interests Section, Japanese Foreign Office, was informed that he had hoped to
                    find practical solution for second British exchange and later for third American
                    exchange but that all <pb facs="0433" n="421" xml:id="pg_421"/> plans for
                    effecting these exchanges have been made much more difficult as result <hi
                        rend="italic">Awa Maru</hi> sinking.<note n="89" xml:id="d296fn1">For
                        documentation on the sinking of this Japanese vessel by an American
                        submarine, see <ref target="#pg_460">pp. 460</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
